<headline>Heat Advisory issued June 27 at 8:08PM MDT until June 28 at 8:00PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque</headline>
<description>...HEAT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM NOON TO 8 PM MDT WEDNESDAY...
* WHAT...Dangerously hot conditions with temperatures up to 107
expected.
* WHERE...Chaves County Plains.
* WHEN...From Noon to 8 PM MDT Wednesday.
* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures may cause heat illnesses.</description>
<instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
